`params_ver2.in` line-by-line reference (for `rc_ver2`)
======================================================

This model (`rc_ver2unix` / `rc_ver2.f`) reads `params_ver2.in` **by position** using a fixed sequence of `READ(8,*)` statements.
That means:

- The **line number matters**.
- The **blank lines matter** (the Fortran code explicitly reads and discards some separator lines).
- There are **no keywords** inside `params_ver2.in`; it is just a list of values.

Below is a mapping for the current `params_ver2.in` in this folder (59 physical lines).

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Integration control (lines 1–10)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Lines 1–3: header/comment lines (skipped by Fortran)

  L1  (skipped)  free text (e.g., "generated by ...")
  L2  (skipped)  blank
  L3  (skipped)  blank

These are read next (1 value per line):

  L4  RESTART     Restart from previous run?                y/n
                 If y: model uses `sounding.out` as initial condition
                 If n: model uses `sounding.in`

  L5  ENDTIME     End time of integration                   days
  L6  DT          Time step                                 minutes
  L7  AVTIME      Averaging time for final profiles          days
  L8  PRINFREQ    Output sampling interval for time series   hours

Separator lines (explicitly read & discarded):

  L9  (skip) blank
  L10 (skip) blank

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Radiation / calendar / surface temperature (lines 11–27)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  L11 RADINT      Interactive radiation?                    y/n
  L12 ICLDS       Interactive clouds?                       y/n
  L13 TSINT       Interactive surface temperature (ocean)?  y/n
                 - For HW (a) "turn off interactive ocean": set this to `n`
                   (then SST stays fixed at the value in `sounding.in`)

  L14 RADFREQ     Frequency of radiation calls              hours
  L15 SCON        Solar constant                             W m^-2
  L16 RLAT        Latitude                                  degrees
  L17 MONTH       Starting month                             integer (1–12)
  L18 IDAY        Starting day                               integer (1–31)
  L19 HOUR        Starting hour                              0–23 (or 1–24)

  L20 TDEP        Time-dependent radiation?                 y/n
  L21 DDEP        Date-dependent radiation?                 y/n
  L22 DARAD       Diurnal-average radiation?                y/n
  L23 ANRAD       Annual-average radiation?                 y/n

  L24 CALB        Calculate ocean albedo?                   y/n
  L25 ALB         Fixed surface albedo (used if CALB='n')   (0–1)

Separator lines (explicitly read & discarded):
  L26 (skip) blank
  L27 (skip) blank

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Well-mixed greenhouse gases + radiative multipliers (lines 28–37)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Mass concentrations (units used by the original model/control file):

  L28 CO2         CO2 concentration                          ppm
  L29 CH4         CH4 concentration                          ppm
  L30 N2O         N2O concentration                          ppb
  L31 CFC11       CFC-11 concentration                       ppt
  L32 CFC12       CFC-12 concentration                       ppt

Water vapor / ozone handling in radiation:

  L33 H2OI        Interactive water vapor?                  y/n
                 If set to 'n', the code also forces ICLDS='n' internally.
  L34 H2OM        Radiation H2O multiplier                   (dimensionless)
  L35 O3M         Radiation O3 multiplier                    (dimensionless)

Separator lines (explicitly read & discarded):
  L36 (skip) blank
  L37 (skip) blank

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
